The paper proposes an approach for explaining Bayesian network classifiers, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of decision functions and algorithms for computing explanations suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of Ordered Decision Diagrams (ODDs) for compiling classifiers suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
